cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper discusses training deep neural networks with biologically plausible learning rules, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on classification tasks using image datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of local learning rules and spiking neurons also suggests a focus on computational neuroscience, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
